  "description": "Proper export and citation preserve attribution and clarify data provenance. This matters for reproducibility and ethical reuse.\n¶Practice guidance Use iNaturalist export tools or GBIF downloads for structured data. Cite both iNaturalist and the specific dataset DOI when using GBIF records. Record the export date and filters used. ¶What goes wrong if you do this poorly Without clear citation, downstream users cannot evaluate provenance or reproduce analyses, weakening credibility and trust.\n",
